\'93You\'92re a difficult man to deal with, Hector,\uc0\u8232 for you don\'92t take advice. God has made you\u8232 more excellent in war than other men.\u8232 Thus, in council you want us all to think\u8232 you\'92re better than the rest. But in yourself\u8232 you can\'92t be everything at once. The gods\u8232 make one man superior in warfare,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[730]\u8232 another in the dance, or singing,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0860\u8232 or playing the lyre. For some others,\u8232 all-seeing Zeus puts wisdom in their hearts\'97\u8232 and from these men many people benefit,\u8232 many are saved, for such men know what\'92s right.\u8232 So I\'92ll say what I think it\'92s best to do.\u8232 All around you war\'92s fiery circle rages,\u8232 but some brave Trojans, having breached the wall,\u8232 are standing idle with their weapons.\u8232 Others, scattered around the ships, fight on\'97\u8232 but in small groups against a larger mass.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0870\u8232 You should fall back, then summon here to you\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[740]\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\u8232 all our finest men. Then we can weigh our options\'97\u8232 whether we should assault the well-decked ships,\u8232 in the hope god wants to give us victory,\u8232 or whether, for safety\'92s sake, we leave the ships.\u8232 I\'92m afraid Achaeans may avenge the hurt\u8232 we gave them yesterday, since by their ships\u8232 there sits a man with appetite for war\'97\u8232 I think he may change his decision not to fight.\'94\
Polydamas finished. His advice pleased Hector.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0880\uc0\u8232 At once he jumped out of his chariot to the ground.\u8232 He took up his weapons and spoke\'97his words had wings:\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[750]\
